\section{The  Kepler problem}
\label{section:Kepler}





In this section, we recall  the (inertial) Kepler problem. The Hamiltonian of the Kepler problem is defined by

text:
\begin{equation}
H  : T^*\big( {\mathbb R}^2 \setminus \left \{ (0,0)\right \} \big) \cong \big( {\mathbb R}^2 \setminus \left \{ (0,0) \right \} \big) \times {\mathbb R} \rightarrow {\mathbb R},\;\;\; (q,p) \mapsto \frac{1}{2}|p|^2 - \frac{1}{|q|}.
\end{equation}

